hackathon-description-text: Our hackathon is part of Major League Hacking's Local Hack Day line up, so hackers will know that they are coding with thousands of other students across the globe.
hackathon-eligibility: Everyone is free to attend, though only projects made by high schoolers will be considered for prizing.
hackathon-requirements: Build whatever you want and have fun with it! Upload whatever you make, so that we can see all the awesome projects people made!
hackathon-rules: Please follow Major League Hacking's Code of Conduct.
hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=3300 Quimby Rd, San Jose, CA 95148, USA
hackathon-location-address: 3300 Quimby Rd, San Jose, CA 95148, USA
hackathon-description-header: Create apps and games to expose the community to the application of computer science.
